Follow the appropriate scenario below.

1. If the document was submitted on the same day the error was discovered:
a) Click on "Docs Sent" link in "Sales";
b) Select the document(s) in question by checking the box in the left column;
c) Click on "Put Selected Documents on Hold" button;
d) Click on the document number to edit the document, change, and re-send.
You will be placed in the document to be edited.

2.  If an invoice has been issued

Follow the steps according to the appropriate scenario below:

2.1 If the dealer billed the wrong account:
a) Go to Financial > Customer Accounting (WOC) Claim;
b) Enter Your Name, Phone Number, Customer Number;
c) Select the reason code;
d) Enter the Invoice Number and Invoice Date;
e) Explain in full description of what needs to be done;
f) Create a new Standard DR for the correct account.

2.2 If the dealer billed at an incorrect price or quantity, or used a wrong nonsig or product code:
a) Go to Financial > Customer Accounting (WOC) Claim;
b) Enter Your Name, Phone Number, Customer Number;
c) Select the reason code;
d) Enter the Invoice Number and Invoice Date;
e) Explain in full description of what needs to be done.

3. Invoice has NOT been issued      (Document was submitted prior to the day the error was discovered.)

3.1 Go to Financial > Reports and check if there is any G86 reports:
a) If there is a G86 report, contact the person listed in the report and provide the information requested;
b) If there is no G86 report, follow the steps according to the appropriate scenario below.

3.2 If the dealer billed at an incorrect price or quantity, or there was a missing requirement, or used a wrong nonsig:
a) Fill out a WOC Claim form- substitute the Invoice #, for the Source Document number.  Type in a detailed explanation in the area provided.

3.3 If the dealer omitted a Product or Service code:
a) Create a new document with a new document number;
b) On the document information screen, choose "Correction" by clicking on the radio button;
c) In the Prompt requesting Return Reference Doc #, enter the source doc # of the original document done in error;
d) In the Prompt requesting Reference Doc Date, enter the document date of the original document done in error;
e) In the Prompt requesting the reason for issuance, explain the reason for issuance;
f) Complete all requirements as before;
g) Add the item(s) omitted.

3.4 If the dealer billed a wrong Product or Service code:
a) Create a new document with a new document number;
b) On the document information screen, choose "Correction" by clicking on the radio button;
c) In the Prompt requesting Return Reference Doc #, enter the source doc # of the original document done in error;
d) In the Prompt requesting Reference Doc Date, enter the document date of the original document done in error;
e) In the Prompt requesting the reason for issuance, explain the reason for issuance;
f) Complete all requirements as before;
g) Debit the correct item(s);
h) Credit the wrong item(s) by putting a minus sign(-) in front of the quantity (fill in the price field if applicable).

NOTE: Never put a minus sign in the quantity field on the first line for a correction document.

3.5 If the dealer billed the wrong account:
a) Go to Financial > Customer Accounting (WOC) Claim;
b) Enter Your Name, Phone Number, Customer Number;
c) Select the reason code;
d) Enter the Invoice Number and Invoice Date;
e) Explain in full description of what needs to be done;  (Doc Voided etc. etc)
d) Create another Standard DR document with a new document number.

